The leading scorer in NBA history is Kareem Abdul-Jabbar, who scored a total of 38,387 points over the course of his career. Abdul-Jabbar played for the Milwaukee Bucks and the Los Angeles Lakers from 1969 to 1989 and is widely regarded as one of the greatest basketball players of all time. His scoring record has stood for many years and is a testament to his longevity and consistent performance over the course of his career.